HEADWORD: Quartette
<hw>Quar*tette"</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>quartetto</ets>, dim. of quarto the fourth,
a fourth part, fr. L. <ets>quartus</ets> the fourth. See
<er>Quart</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
composition in four parts, each performed by a single voice or
instrument.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The set of four person who perform a
piece of music in four parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Poet.)</fld> <def>A stanza of four lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quartic</ent>⟦br⟧
